ENTRY       EC 2.3.1.153                Enzyme
NAME        anthocyanin 5-(6'''-hydroxycinnamoyltransferase)
CLASS       Transferases;
            Acyltransferases;
            Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
SYSNAME     4-hydroxycinnamoyl-CoA:anthocyanidin 3,5-diglucoside 5-O-glucoside-6'''-O-4-hydroxycinnamoyltransferase
REACTION    4-hydroxycinnamoyl-CoA + anthocyanidin 3,5-diglucoside = CoA + anthocyanidin 3-glucoside 5-(6-O-4-hydroxycinnamoylglucoside) [RN:R05163]
ALL_REAC    R05163 > R07880 R07882 R07883 R07930 R07931 R07944
SUBSTRATE   4-hydroxycinnamoyl-CoA [CPD:C00223];
            anthocyanidin 3,5-diglucoside
PRODUCT     CoA [CPD:C00010];
            anthocyanidin 3-glucoside 5-(6-O-4-hydroxycinnamoylglucoside)
COMMENT     Isolated from the plant Gentiana triflora. Transfers the hydroxycinnamoyl group only to the C-5 glucoside of anthocyanin. Caffeoyl-CoA, but not malonyl-CoA, can substitute as an acyl donor.
HISTORY     EC 2.3.1.153 created 1999, modified 2013
